    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Pungent yellow powder of the seeds of any of several common mustard plants, used as a condiment, dye, or in medicine as a stimulant and diuretic, an emetic, or a counterirritant.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
